alert.note: Alert for Coastal Del Norte; Northern Humboldt Coast (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 23 at 2:17PM PST until February 23 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING BELOW 1000 FEET... * WHAT...Snow below 1000 feet. Additional snow accumulations of up to two inches. Sea level locations can expect less than an inch. * WHAT.Snow below 1000 feet. Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch. * WHERE...Coastal Del Norte and Northern Humboldt Coast Counties. * WHEN...Until 10 PM PST this evening. * IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous conditions could impact the evening commute.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions for the state of California can be obtained by calling 1-800-GAS-ROAD.
